comment: Alternate definition of a subcategory, as a subset of the category which is itself a category. The assumption that the identity be closed is necessary just as in the case of a monoid, ~ issubm2 , for the same reasons, since categories are a generalization of monoids. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 6-Jan-2017.)
